The paper focuses on testing robotic software, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Belief-Desire-Intention (BDI) agents as models for test generation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The comparison of different test generation methods suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The testing of robots as home care assistants suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the use of simulators and automated testbenches suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
